The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 11, 2009, as Patriot Day and National Day of Service and Remembrance. The proclamation acknowledges the tragic events of September 11, 2001, and honors the lives lost on that day. It calls for unity, justice, and the defense of national security. The proclamation also recognizes the National Day of Service and Remembrance as an opportunity to salute the heroes of 9/11 and engage in meaningful service activities to support communities. The President encourages all Americans to participate in community service and observe a moment of silence at 8:46 am, the time when the first attack occurred. The proclamation also requests the display of the American flag at half-staff on this day.